<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,400,715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
1. Antenniferous tubercles armed with short spiny projection; humeri with one stout conical protuberance; calli with deep hole, behind posterior third; anterolateral margins of pronotum with one conical protuberance; posterior half of connexival segments III–VI conspicuously swollen; hemelytral membrane absent; postocular tubercle hemispheric, faintly insinuate over the surface (
<figureCitation box="[233,300,488,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1676,1700]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,429,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-114@2.[151,1436,417,1653]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Dorsal view of Monasavuhygia spp. 1, M. cordata Brailovsky, 1996 (female). 2, M. fodina sp. nov. (female). 3, M. incola sp. nov. (female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5851261/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[311,325,488,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1432,1456]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,322,1395]" captionTargetId="figure-67@3.[151,1436,309,1409]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–6. Female genital plates in caudal view of Monasavuhygia spp. 4, M. cordata Brailovsky, 1996. 5, M. fodina sp. nov. 6, M. incola sp. nov. FIGURES 7–9. Female genital plates in lateral view of Monasavuhygia spp. 7, M. cordata Brailovsky, 1996. 8, M. fodina sp. nov. 9, M. incola sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5851263/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">6</figureCitation>
, 9)........................................................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1076,1253,487,509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="496">
<taxonomicName authority="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera, 2022" authorityName="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera" authorityYear="2022" box="[1076,1171,487,509]" class="Insecta" family="Coreidae" genus="Monasavuhygia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incola" status="sp. nov.">
